Suning Appliance First-Quarter Net Rises on Store Expansion

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-04-29T13:05:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/suning-appliance-first-quarter-net-rises-on-store-expansion-1-.html
Suning Appliance Co.,  China ’s
largest electronics retailer by market value, said first-quarter
profit climbed 27 percent as it opened more outlets to cater to
rising demand.  Net income climbed to 1.12 billion yuan ($173 million) from
883.8 million yuan a year earlier, Suning said in a filing to
 Shanghai ’s stock exchange today. Sales increased 23 percent to
20.6 billion yuan. The company had 1,348 stores on March 31,
compared with 962 outlets a year earlier.  Suning and Gome Electrical Appliances Holding Ltd. compete
for market share in China’s electronics and appliance market,
where sales are expected to surge to 2.14 trillion yuan in 2015,
from 1.26 trillion yuan in 2010, according to London-based
Euromonitor International.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Longid at 
 flongid@bloomberg.net  